2
00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:34.280
What is this?

3
00:01:34.700 --> 00:01:36.980
Don't you have other things to do
besides this?

4
00:01:37.660 --> 00:01:39.600
Sorry sir. this lane is closed temporarily.

5
00:01:39.720 --> 00:01:42.060
You can turn around through the other way.

6
00:01:42.220 --> 00:01:43.500
Please understand.

7
00:01:43.760 --> 00:01:45.160
Go on.

8
00:01:45.200 --> 00:01:47.100
But I'm gonna be late!

9
00:01:48.520 --> 00:01:50.100
This is a very important package.

10
00:01:50.100 --> 00:01:51.450
If this package is not delivered on time--

11
00:01:51.900 --> 00:01:53.280
Who do you think will be responsible?

12
00:01:53.660 --> 00:01:58.840
Geez. Okay. Just be quick. all right?

13
00:01:59.680 --> 00:02:01.000
You can pass.

14
00:02:01.260 --> 00:02:02.240
Come on.

15
00:02:07.260 --> 00:02:09.440
What a really bad day...

16
00:02:11.140 --> 00:02:13.240
Rough morning. What more...

17
00:02:19.160 --> 00:02:19.900
Dammit!

18
00:02:20.160 --> 00:02:21.100
Dammit!

19
00:02:45.260 --> 00:02:47.200
As if anything else could go worse!

20
00:03:36.360 --> 00:03:41.400
"TRAIN TO BUSAN"

21
00:03:42.320 --> 00:03:43.160
Sunbaenim.

22
00:03:43.620 --> 00:03:47.500
statistical data companies showed
abnormal stock market returns.

23
00:03:47.760 --> 00:03:50.040
What we need is to take action
as soon as possible.

24
00:03:50.240 --> 00:03:52.260
in order to secure our position
in the stock market.

25
00:03:54.200 --> 00:03:54.860
Yes.

26
00:03:54.960 --> 00:03:56.000
Thank you for the instructions.

27
00:03:59.600 --> 00:04:03.360
I will do it as soon as possible.

28
00:04:04.400 --> 00:04:05.260
Yes.

29
00:04:05.560 --> 00:04:07.460
It will be done as you wish.

30
00:04:08.360 --> 00:04:09.180
Yeah. yeah.

31
00:04:09.220 --> 00:04:10.160
Have a nice day.

32
00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:28.100
Come into my office.

33
00:04:45.560 --> 00:04:46.480
Yes. sir?

34
00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:48.880
Secure all of our assets in the stock market.

35
00:04:49.460 --> 00:04:50.400
All of them?

36
00:04:50.850 --> 00:04:51.400
Yes.

37
00:04:52.050 --> 00:04:54.160
Is it not too risky to do this?

38
00:04:54.560 --> 00:04:56.350
We could still maintain our first assets

39
00:04:56.500 --> 00:04:58.300
and wait if something better comes...

40
00:04:58.300 --> 00:04:59.040
Mr. Kim.

41
00:04:59.700 --> 00:05:00.360
Yes. sir?

42
00:05:01.400 --> 00:05:03.400
You just do what I tell you to do.

43
00:05:05.680 --> 00:05:07.680
We must be careful
of the possibilities that may happen.

44
00:05:08.900 --> 00:05:09.480
Yes. sir.

45
00:05:12.620 --> 00:05:13.760
One more thing Mr. Kim.

46
00:05:16.600 --> 00:05:19.340
What's the popular gift for kids nowadays?

47
00:05:25.220 --> 00:05:29.300
<i>Forget it. You really can't be a good dad to Soo-an.
You didn't even attend her recital.</i>

48
00:05:29.600 --> 00:05:32.240
You know I'm busy at work.

49
00:05:32.320 --> 00:05:33.340
She can stay here in Seoul with me.

50
00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:35.900
<i>Just bring her to Busan.</i>

51
00:05:36.340 --> 00:05:37.900
<i>You already broke your promises!</i>

52
00:05:39.300 --> 00:05:42.040
<i>You're supposed to bring Soo-an here tomorrow.</i>

53
00:05:42.760 --> 00:05:43.900
<i>Did you know that?</i>

54
00:05:44.180 --> 00:05:45.900
What are you talking about?

55
00:05:47.100 --> 00:05:48.900
<i>I can't believe you.</i>

56
00:05:49.060 --> 00:05:50.740
How can I let her go alone?

57
00:05:51.100 --> 00:05:52.800
<i>Then take her along with you.</i>

58
00:05:53.360 --> 00:05:54.900
<i>She said she misses me.</i>

59
00:05:55.180 --> 00:05:56.200
I can't go tomorrow.

60
00:05:56.680 --> 00:05:58.980
<i>You know it's her birthday tomorrow. right?</i>

61
00:05:59.500 --> 00:06:00.440
I know!

62
00:06:28.700 --> 00:06:29.720
Let me help you with that.

63
00:06:30.200 --> 00:06:31.120
Thank you.

64
00:06:31.680 --> 00:06:32.460
How is she?

65
00:06:33.860 --> 00:06:36.740
She's playing in her room.

66
00:06:38.620 --> 00:06:40.840
When are we going there?

67
00:06:42.080 --> 00:06:45.300
But mom. haven't you talked to daddy yet?

68
00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:51.600
I have to go. Daddy's here.

69
00:07:05.300 --> 00:07:06.700
It's fine. you can talk to her.

70
00:07:06.940 --> 00:07:08.300
I already hung up.

71
00:07:11.600 --> 00:07:13.660
Your mom called me earlier.

72
00:07:15.380 --> 00:07:18.520
I promised her we'll go together.

73
00:07:20.360 --> 00:07:22.240
But before that.
there are things I have to do.

74
00:07:22.580 --> 00:07:24.300
Soo-an you have to be patient.

75
00:07:33.320 --> 00:07:34.300
Open it.

76
00:07:38.780 --> 00:07:40.140
You thought I forgot?

77
00:07:40.341 --> 00:07:41.500
Happy birthday.

78
00:07:43.400 --> 00:07:44.600
Open it now.

79
00:08:02.140 --> 00:08:04.660
What's wrong?
Don't you like it?

80
00:08:19.100 --> 00:08:20.800
It's just like last year.

81
00:08:26.940 --> 00:08:28.000
Well then.

82
00:08:28.480 --> 00:08:29.900
what do you want?

83
00:08:31.660 --> 00:08:32.640
Busan.

84
00:08:33.220 --> 00:08:35.300
I want to visit mom in Busan.

85
00:08:35.980 --> 00:08:36.700
Tomorrow.

86
00:08:37.160 --> 00:08:38.760
I just told you...

87
00:08:39.220 --> 00:08:41.160
We'll certainly go there
once dad is done with work.

88
00:08:41.260 --> 00:08:42.000
No.

89
00:08:42.400 --> 00:08:43.360
Tomorrow.

90
00:08:44.100 --> 00:08:46.100
You always tell me
we will go next time but we don't.

91
00:08:46.180 --> 00:08:47.800
We have to go tomorrow
no matter what.

92
00:08:49.320 --> 00:08:51.320
Daddy is always working. all the time.

93
00:08:51.800 --> 00:08:53.500
It's always been like that.

94
00:09:01.200 --> 00:09:02.700
What did your daughter say?

95
00:09:03.500 --> 00:09:05.000
She wants us to have a vacation.

96
00:09:06.100 --> 00:09:09.000
Does she want to go to Busan?

97
00:09:10.640 --> 00:09:11.520
Yes.

98
00:09:12.240 --> 00:09:17.020
You should try and talk to your wife
when you arrive there.

99
00:09:18.540 --> 00:09:22.200
Meet with her
and have a good meal together.

100
00:09:22.320 --> 00:09:24.260
Talk it over properly this time.

101
00:09:25.580 --> 00:09:28.900
Divorce is never easy.
especially for the children.

102
00:09:31.480 --> 00:09:33.540
Think about it.
even just for Soo-an's sake.

103
00:09:33.600 --> 00:09:34.380
Mom.

104
00:09:34.580 --> 00:09:35.940
I don't want to talk about it.

105
00:09:39.280 --> 00:09:41.020
It's all in the past.

106
00:09:43.440 --> 00:09:44.240
Okay.

107
00:09:45.420 --> 00:09:48.140
Don't be too busy with work.

108
00:09:50.180 --> 00:09:53.160
You shouldn't always focus on work.
Soo-an is growing up.

109
00:09:53.700 --> 00:09:55.280
She also needs you.

110
00:09:56.860 --> 00:10:00.680
Take care of your family. especially Soo-an.

111
00:10:43.000 --> 00:10:44.900
<i>Come on Soo-an. cheer up!</i>

112
00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:47.900
<i>It's okay. continue singing.</i>

113
00:10:48.560 --> 00:10:51.900
<i>Please give a round of applause
to Soo-an!</i>

114
00:11:04.824 --> 00:11:05.824
<i>Okay.</i>

115
00:11:06.280 --> 00:11:07.300
<i>Yes. mom.</i>

116
00:11:08.120 --> 00:11:08.880
<i>Okay.</i>

117
00:11:09.940 --> 00:11:10.840
No.

118
00:11:11.080 --> 00:11:12.420
I'm with daddy.

119
00:11:14.960 --> 00:11:17.600
Yeah. see you there.

120
00:11:34.020 --> 00:11:37.600
Hey Soo-an.
why didn't you finish your song?

121
00:11:38.120 --> 00:11:41.100
How did you know?
You weren't even there.

122
00:11:42.780 --> 00:11:46.600
Dad always knows what you're doing.

123
00:11:48.320 --> 00:11:49.600
You got nervous. right?

124
00:11:50.320 --> 00:11:51.260
Am I right?

125
00:11:52.080 --> 00:11:52.960
Yes.

126
00:11:54.440 --> 00:11:56.880
You know you have to finish that song.

127
00:11:58.340 --> 00:12:02.140
Whenever you start something.
you must finish it. no matter what.

128
00:12:03.000 --> 00:12:04.700
Always remember that.

129
00:12:16.520 --> 00:12:17.980
Woah. that was close.

130
00:12:22.700 --> 00:12:24.680
What's going on so early in the morning?

131
00:12:32.200 --> 00:12:34.240
Soo-an. are you okay?
Were you scared?

132
00:12:35.620 --> 00:12:37.160
That was really close...

133
00:12:48.480 --> 00:12:50.700
Something must have happened
over there. Soo-an.

134
00:13:04.600 --> 00:13:10.830
<i>To all passengers. kindly board the train now.
The train will depart for Busan shortly.</i>

135
00:13:11.131 --> 00:13:14.260
<i>I repeat. the train to Busan is departing shortly.</i>

136
00:13:14.260 --> 00:13:15.700
Excuse me. where is the south station?

137
00:13:15.720 --> 00:13:17.440
Ah. South station.
you need to go that way.

138
00:13:17.440 --> 00:13:18.360
Thank you.

139
00:13:46.500 --> 00:13:48.800
Wait. Hae-yong. Your scarf...

140
00:13:56.780 --> 00:13:59.940
Now everyone. keep quiet
and use this trip to rest. okay?

141
00:14:00.020 --> 00:14:01.240
Yes!

142
00:14:03.980 --> 00:14:05.900
Wow. Jin-hee is here.

143
00:14:08.801 --> 00:14:10.301
Hey. what are you doing here?

144
00:14:10.400 --> 00:14:12.640
What do you mean?
I'm coming with you guys.

145
00:14:12.680 --> 00:14:14.240
-  Really?
- I'm your cheerleader.

146
00:14:14.241 --> 00:14:15.241
That's awesome!

147
00:14:15.242 --> 00:14:16.242
Amazing.

148
00:14:17.500 --> 00:14:18.500
How are you guys doing?

149
00:14:18.540 --> 00:14:19.660
Good.

150
00:14:20.740 --> 00:14:24.480
- Hello. hello.
- Jin-hee. hello.

151
00:14:24.800 --> 00:14:26.040
Finally!

152
00:14:28.700 --> 00:14:30.960
Hey. it's rude to take something
that isn't yours.

153
00:14:31.300 --> 00:14:32.780
You really hate to share.

154
00:14:33.080 --> 00:14:37.140
Hey. maybe if we're lovers.
you'll be thankful and share with me.

155
00:14:37.160 --> 00:14:39.380
I might even share my bed with you.

156
00:14:39.380 --> 00:14:42.460
Wow. that's very tempting.

157
00:14:43.000 --> 00:14:46.240
Share with her! Share with her!

158
00:14:46.441 --> 00:14:49.080
Share with her!

159
00:14:53.300 --> 00:14:54.260
Here. eat this.

160
00:14:55.300 --> 00:14:57.220
Goodness. what year are you from?

161
00:14:57.520 --> 00:15:00.080
Don't eat a lot of eggs.
You'll end up passing gas later.

162
00:15:00.260 --> 00:15:01.080
I don't want it.

163
00:15:01.160 --> 00:15:03.100
- Eat it.
- No. thanks.

164
00:15:04.640 --> 00:15:06.410
<i>Sir. are you on the train?</i>

165
00:15:06.811 --> 00:15:08.480
Yes. we're on the train.

166
00:15:08.740 --> 00:15:10.770
<i>The lines were busy since this morning.</i>

167
00:15:10.771 --> 00:15:13.400
<i>The Ansan plant leak last night
got everyone frantic.</i>

168
00:15:13.960 --> 00:15:14.840
Is that so?

169
00:15:16.340 --> 00:15:18.340
We'll discuss it later once I get back.

170
00:15:18.480 --> 00:15:20.640
I'll be back later after lunch.

171
00:15:20.940 --> 00:15:23.020
- I'll see you later.
<i>- Understood.</i>

172
00:16:28.000 --> 00:16:29.485
This can't be happening.

173
00:16:29.486 --> 00:16:30.970
I'm so sorry.

174
00:16:31.171 --> 00:16:32.805
Please forgive me.

175
00:16:33.506 --> 00:16:35.340
I'm so sorry.

176
00:16:36.000 --> 00:16:37.520
Please don't let this happen!

177
00:16:47.800 --> 00:16:49.300
- Excuse me?
- Yes.

178
00:16:50.660 --> 00:16:52.220
- Are you the one in charge?
- Yes.

179
00:16:52.780 --> 00:16:54.230
There's a suspiscious man inside.

180
00:16:54.631 --> 00:16:55.680
Where?

181
00:16:56.040 --> 00:16:58.220
Inside the washroom.

182
00:16:59.440 --> 00:17:01.520
I'm afraid something happened to him.

183
00:17:01.600 --> 00:17:02.700
Yes. he's taking so long.

184
00:17:04.240 --> 00:17:05.500
I apologize for that.

185
00:17:05.601 --> 00:17:07.360
- Let me have a look.
- All right.

186
00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:18.820
Sir?

187
00:17:21.500 --> 00:17:22.500
Sir?

188
00:17:26.100 --> 00:17:27.040
Sir?

189
00:17:37.780 --> 00:17:38.620
Sir?

190
00:17:40.040 --> 00:17:40.880
Sir?

191
00:17:41.660 --> 00:17:43.720
Do you have a ticket?

192
00:17:46.740 --> 00:17:49.220
Sir. do you have a ticket?

193
00:17:49.320 --> 00:17:52.500
If you don't. we need to drop you off
at the next station.

194
00:17:53.580 --> 00:17:54.840
Everyone is dead.

195
00:17:56.840 --> 00:17:58.420
- Everyone is dead.
- What?

196
00:18:06.320 --> 00:18:07.500
Hey. little girl.

197
00:18:08.100 --> 00:18:10.500
If you don't study well.
you will end up just like him.

198
00:18:11.480 --> 00:18:15.500
My mom says people who talk rudely
about others are bad people.

199
00:18:16.800 --> 00:18:19.500
I guess your mom
didn't study hard to succeed then.

200
00:18:19.820 --> 00:18:21.800
Sir. you must come with me to the back.

201
00:18:22.501 --> 00:18:24.501
Sir. please. you have to get out of there.

202
00:19:00.260 --> 00:19:01.280
Do you need to pee?

203
00:19:02.860 --> 00:19:05.520
Well. you need to use another one
since there are two people inside.

204
00:19:06.420 --> 00:19:08.820
You can use that one there.
Go ahead.

205
00:19:12.320 --> 00:19:13.940
This will really take a while.

206
00:19:14.760 --> 00:19:17.420
Honey. how are you doing there?

207
00:19:18.820 --> 00:19:21.500
All right. sorry.
Go ahead and take your time.

208
00:19:21.600 --> 00:19:22.880
Please. go ahead.

209
00:19:23.060 --> 00:19:24.480
Go there. use the other one.

210
00:19:26.200 --> 00:19:29.880
All right. she's gone.
Just relax now. Relax.

211
00:19:39.200 --> 00:19:41.440
Miss? Are you okay?

212
00:19:41.660 --> 00:19:43.480
Miss? What do I do?

213
00:19:45.180 --> 00:19:47.680
There's an emergency at car 11!

214
00:19:48.140 --> 00:19:48.920
Chief!

215
00:20:02.920 --> 00:20:03.690
<i>Hello?</i>

216
00:20:03.691 --> 00:20:04.460
Yes. Mr. Kim?

217
00:20:04.480 --> 00:20:06.960
<i>It's more serious than we anticipated.</i>

218
00:20:07.200 --> 00:20:09.200
<i>It's not just an overnight Ansan incident.</i>

219
00:20:09.620 --> 00:20:13.960
<i>I don't know whats happening.
but it's not a simple strike.</i>

220
00:20:14.040 --> 00:20:16.230
MILITARY DEPLOYED TO CONTROL RIOTS
<i>- They say it's nationwide.</i>

221
00:20:16.340 --> 00:20:18.860
<i>- What about her breathing?
- Hello?</i>

222
00:20:19.000 --> 00:20:22.840
<i>I'm doing everything I can
but nothing seems to work!</i>

223
00:20:23.260 --> 00:20:24.780
<i>Sir. what should we do?</i>

224
00:20:25.200 --> 00:20:26.680
I'll call you back.

225
00:20:36.000 --> 00:20:37.610
VIOLENCE ERUPTS AT RIOT

226
00:20:37.811 --> 00:20:40.220
Oh no. they'll get hurt.

227
00:20:40.500 --> 00:20:41.880
That's terrible.

228
00:20:42.000 --> 00:20:44.760
People nowadays will start a riot
over everything.

229
00:20:45.000 --> 00:20:47.860
If this was in the old days.
they will be re-educated.

230
00:20:47.900 --> 00:20:49.400
Stop saying that.

231
00:20:51.600 --> 00:20:52.588
Oh my.

232
00:20:54.040 --> 00:20:55.480
Goodness. just look at them...

233
00:20:56.940 --> 00:20:57.780
Miss?

234
00:21:00.100 --> 00:21:00.960
What do I do?

235
00:21:04.660 --> 00:21:07.120
Chief? Chief. where are you?

236
00:21:09.920 --> 00:21:11.420
I don't believe this...

237
00:21:21.600 --> 00:21:22.540
Chief?

238
00:21:38.220 --> 00:21:39.070
Min-jin?

239
00:21:39.220 --> 00:21:40.180
Min-jin?

240
00:22:07.720 --> 00:22:08.600
What's that?

241
00:22:11.380 --> 00:22:12.520
What's happening?

242
00:22:14.700 --> 00:22:15.600
What the hell?

243
00:22:18.601 --> 00:22:19.601
Help him!

244
00:22:30.580 --> 00:22:31.590
Excuse me.

245
00:22:31.791 --> 00:22:32.795
Excuse me.

246
00:22:32.996 --> 00:22:33.800
Excuse me.

247
00:22:57.069 --> 00:22:58.968
Everybody. run! Hurry!

248
00:22:59.069 --> 00:23:00.069
Stand up!

249
00:23:03.180 --> 00:23:04.920
Conductor! We have a situation here!

250
00:23:04.921 --> 00:23:07.660
Conductor!
I need some help here. please!

251
00:23:20.860 --> 00:23:21.760
Run! Run!

252
00:23:42.921 --> 00:23:45.421
- Oh my god!
- What's going on?

253
00:23:56.000 --> 00:23:57.480
Get away! Just go!

254
00:24:04.260 --> 00:24:07.090
Run! Head for the back!

255
00:24:07.190 --> 00:24:08.540
Get up! Hurry!

256
00:24:30.720 --> 00:24:31.580
Daddy!

257
00:25:14.040 --> 00:25:14.820
Honey?

258
00:25:16.440 --> 00:25:19.160
Hey. Sang-Hwa! It's so loud!

259
00:25:19.220 --> 00:25:21.210
Sorry. but the thing is...

260
00:25:21.440 --> 00:25:22.800
Get off me!

261
00:25:34.285 --> 00:25:35.817
You idiot! Go help her!

262
00:25:38.440 --> 00:25:39.140
Hey!

263
00:25:39.220 --> 00:25:40.760
What's up with you?

264
00:25:44.360 --> 00:25:45.600
Are you crazy?

265
00:26:00.820 --> 00:26:01.600
Honey?

266
00:26:02.620 --> 00:26:03.720
Hey. Sung-Gyeong!

267
00:26:06.420 --> 00:26:07.800
You can run. right?

268
00:26:24.940 --> 00:26:27.580
CASUALTIES INCREASE
DUE TO MASSIVE VIOLENCE

269
00:26:27.881 --> 00:26:28.881
Run!

270
00:26:29.040 --> 00:26:29.940
Get away!

271
00:26:41.100 --> 00:26:42.780
The door! Get the door!

272
00:26:44.160 --> 00:26:45.160
Close the door!

273
00:26:46.520 --> 00:26:47.590
Hurry!

274
00:26:48.840 --> 00:26:49.800
Close it!

275
00:26:51.380 --> 00:26:52.560
Close it now!

276
00:26:53.361 --> 00:26:54.361
Hurry!

277
00:26:54.400 --> 00:26:55.900
Just close it!

278
00:27:03.470 --> 00:27:04.760
I know that man!

279
00:27:17.760 --> 00:27:19.280
How do you lock this?

280
00:27:20.380 --> 00:27:22.260
Hey. how do I lock this?

281
00:27:24.560 --> 00:27:25.920
Hey. are you listening?

282
00:27:29.880 --> 00:27:30.960
Let it go.

283
00:27:32.040 --> 00:27:32.920
What?

284
00:27:35.980 --> 00:27:38.180
I don't think they know how to open it.

285
00:27:48.400 --> 00:27:50.120
They only attack when they see us.

286
00:28:11.520 --> 00:28:12.650
What in the world--?

287
00:28:12.940 --> 00:28:14.140
What are those things?

288
00:28:18.460 --> 00:28:19.560
Soo-an. are you okay?

289
00:28:21.535 --> 00:28:22.535
Hey. you.

290
00:28:23.860 --> 00:28:24.720
What is it?

291
00:28:26.660 --> 00:28:28.460
Don't you owe me an apology?

292
00:28:28.800 --> 00:28:29.810
What do you mean?

293
00:28:30.440 --> 00:28:31.620
Look at this chump.

294
00:28:32.410 --> 00:28:35.340
You shut the door in our faces. asshole!

295
00:28:35.440 --> 00:28:37.720
You weren't the only ones in danger!

296
00:28:39.320 --> 00:28:40.860
What a piece of work.

297
00:28:41.940 --> 00:28:42.820
Come here.

298
00:28:42.860 --> 00:28:44.520
I'm gonna feed you to them.

299
00:28:44.674 --> 00:28:45.674
Stop it!

300
00:28:46.060 --> 00:28:47.640
Everyone's just scared.

301
00:28:52.600 --> 00:28:54.500
<i>Attention please!</i>

302
00:28:54.820 --> 00:28:57.500
<i>Due to our current situation.</i>

303
00:28:57.601 --> 00:28:59.980
<i>we won't be stopping at Cheonan station.</i>

304
00:29:00.520 --> 00:29:03.800
<i>For your own safety.
please stay on your seats.</i>

305
00:29:05.701 --> 00:29:06.701
Excuse me.

306
00:29:09.240 --> 00:29:11.080
Hello? Is anyone there?

307
00:29:11.750 --> 00:29:13.440
<i>Yes. go ahead.</i>

308
00:29:13.520 --> 00:29:17.280
Do you have any idea
on the situation here right now?

309
00:29:17.520 --> 00:29:19.460
Why aren't we stopping at Cheonan station?

310
00:29:19.480 --> 00:29:20.740
<i>We're aware. sir.</i>

311
00:29:20.800 --> 00:29:23.840
<i>But this is a direct order
from the control center.</i>

312
00:29:24.170 --> 00:29:25.400
<i>Please return to your seats.</i>

313
00:29:25.580 --> 00:29:27.570
That's nonsense!

314
00:29:27.671 --> 00:29:30.160
There are people turning rabid
and they're attacking others!

315
00:29:30.680 --> 00:29:32.560
Stop in Cheonan. understood?

316
00:29:34.360 --> 00:29:35.380
Hold on a second.

317
00:29:39.340 --> 00:29:42.240
I'm so sorry.
but can she take this seat?

318
00:29:42.460 --> 00:29:43.560
She's pregnant.

319
00:29:43.860 --> 00:29:44.570
Of course.

320
00:29:44.880 --> 00:29:45.705
Sit down.

321
00:29:45.706 --> 00:29:46.530
Thank you.

322
00:29:46.640 --> 00:29:48.860
MOTHER

323
00:29:50.560 --> 00:29:51.420
Yes. mom?

324
00:29:51.567 --> 00:29:55.067
<i>Are you on your way to Busan?</i>

325
00:29:56.220 --> 00:29:57.640
Yes. we're on our way.

326
00:29:58.600 --> 00:30:00.700
Where are you? Why is it so loud?

327
00:30:00.860 --> 00:30:02.780
<i>What's happening?</i>

328
00:30:02.981 --> 00:30:04.900
<i>Everyone's fighting.</i>

329
00:30:05.260 --> 00:30:08.560
<i>Are you and Soo-an okay?</i>

330
00:30:09.080 --> 00:30:11.240
Why are you breathing like that?
Are you hurt?

331
00:30:12.900 --> 00:30:15.440
<i>Seok-Woo. my son.</i>

332
00:30:16.020 --> 00:30:20.760
<i>Please take care of Soo-an.</i>

333
00:30:21.080 --> 00:30:22.140
Mom. are you okay?

334
00:30:23.740 --> 00:30:26.120
<i>My dear Soo-an...</i>

335
00:30:29.660 --> 00:30:35.320
<i>I love her so much.
but she only wants her mother.</i>

336
00:30:38.080 --> 00:30:39.620
<i>That bitch!</i>

337
00:30:48.020 --> 00:30:48.900
Mom?

338
00:30:51.700 --> 00:30:52.440
<i>Daddy.</i>

339
00:30:54.959 --> 00:30:55.959
<i>Daddy!</i>

340
00:30:58.020 --> 00:30:59.880
Is grandma okay?

341
00:31:08.420 --> 00:31:09.820
What the hell?

342
00:31:11.620 --> 00:31:13.140
Soo-an. sit down.

343
00:31:58.020 --> 00:31:59.640
<i>My fellow citizens.</i>

344
00:32:00.461 --> 00:32:06.961
<i>we're currently experiencing
violent riots in all major cities.</i>

345
00:32:07.438 --> 00:32:11.938
<i>resulting in many civilians and police injuries.</i>

346
00:32:12.740 --> 00:32:17.120
<i>These riots led to the shut down
of various districts</i>

347
00:32:17.390 --> 00:32:21.980
<i>and the rioters have forcibly
attempted to destroy</i>

348
00:32:22.340 --> 00:32:24.840
<i>and take over government property.</i>

349
00:32:26.660 --> 00:32:30.000
<i>For this reason.
we're entering a state of emergency</i>

350
00:32:30.870 --> 00:32:37.040
<i>in order to control the current situation.</i>

351
00:32:39.560 --> 00:32:45.580
<i>Thanks to our government's quick response.</i>

352
00:32:46.240 --> 00:32:49.620
<i>various outbreaks are being contained.</i>

353
00:32:51.178 --> 00:32:52.242
<i>Fellow citizens.</i>

354
00:32:52.880 --> 00:32:58.540
<i>please refrain from reacting to baseless rumors.</i>

355
00:32:59.120 --> 00:33:04.580
<i>and stay in the safety of your homes.</i>

356
00:33:05.134 --> 00:33:08.000
<i>We must stay calm and trust the government.</i>

357
00:33:08.340 --> 00:33:11.500
<i>in order to overcome such trying obstacle.</i>

358
00:33:12.600 --> 00:33:16.340
<i>We believe that your safety is not in jeopardy.</i>

359
00:33:30.160 --> 00:33:31.200
ANALYST KIM

360
00:33:38.140 --> 00:33:39.990
Mom's phone is turned off.

361
00:33:44.096 --> 00:33:47.096
<i>Those in front. hurry up!</i>

362
00:33:47.525 --> 00:33:49.025
Soo-an. sit here first.

363
00:33:49.663 --> 00:33:51.963
Don't worry.
I'll give your mom a call.

364
00:33:54.005 --> 00:33:55.605
Jong-Gil. come and take a seat first.

365
00:33:56.080 --> 00:33:58.360
You're older than me.
You should sit.

366
00:33:58.380 --> 00:33:59.500
I'm fine. just sit down.

367
00:33:59.660 --> 00:34:01.020
Honey. let's go over there.

368
00:34:01.021 --> 00:34:02.021
All right.

369
00:34:05.740 --> 00:34:08.080
Grandma. you can take my seat.

370
00:34:08.160 --> 00:34:09.490
I'm okay. you can sit down.

371
00:34:09.591 --> 00:34:11.220
No. you can take it.

372
00:34:15.180 --> 00:34:15.960
Dear girl.

373
00:34:17.030 --> 00:34:17.960
You can have this.

374
00:34:21.180 --> 00:34:22.760
Thank you.

375
00:34:23.120 --> 00:34:24.470
What a nice girl.

376
00:34:29.029 --> 00:34:29.929
We both got seats.

377
00:34:30.130 --> 00:34:31.730
Keep walking. hurry.

378
00:34:32.731 --> 00:34:33.731
<i>That bag...</i>

379
00:34:35.460 --> 00:34:37.720
Soo-an. you didn't have to do that.

380
00:34:38.480 --> 00:34:39.670
Do what?

381
00:34:39.871 --> 00:34:40.960
Being nice.

382
00:34:41.420 --> 00:34:44.120
In times like this. only watch out for yourself.
Understood?

383
00:34:47.413 --> 00:34:48.413
Answer me.

384
00:34:53.620 --> 00:34:56.800
Grandma always had aching knees.

385
00:34:58.452 --> 00:34:59.452
Soo-an...

386
00:35:04.840 --> 00:35:07.700
<i>May I have your attention please?</i>

387
00:35:08.300 --> 00:35:11.900
<i>This train's last stop
will be at Daejeon Station.</i>

388
00:35:12.620 --> 00:35:17.930
<i>The army is deployed there
and will secure the train.</i>

389
00:35:18.380 --> 00:35:22.000
<i>Once we arrive. please alight the train.</i>

390
00:35:22.300 --> 00:35:23.740
<i>I repeat.</i>

391
00:35:24.380 --> 00:35:26.920
<i>Daejeon station will be our last stop.</i>

392
00:35:27.280 --> 00:35:29.400
What are the cities that can be entered?

393
00:35:29.753 --> 00:35:32.420
Yeosu. Uljin. Busan.
What about Daejeon?

394
00:35:32.960 --> 00:35:34.540
Excuse me. I need to use it.

395
00:35:34.800 --> 00:35:36.100
What about Daejeon?

396
00:35:36.590 --> 00:35:37.440
<i>Why not?</i>

397
00:35:39.580 --> 00:35:41.940
Soo-an. wait here for a bit.

398
00:35:46.040 --> 00:35:46.860
Hey. kiddo.

399
00:35:47.640 --> 00:35:48.360
Yes?

400
00:35:48.620 --> 00:35:50.330
Who is he? Is that your dad?

401
00:35:51.320 --> 00:35:52.040
Yes.

402
00:35:52.290 --> 00:35:53.820
- Real dad?
- Yes.

403
00:35:54.770 --> 00:35:55.980
I was just making sure.

404
00:35:57.240 --> 00:35:58.500
What does he do?

405
00:35:58.750 --> 00:36:00.750
He's a fund manager.

406
00:36:00.958 --> 00:36:03.157
- Ah. a fund manager?
- Yes.

407
00:36:04.043 --> 00:36:05.643
He's a bloodsucker. a bloodsucker.

408
00:36:06.700 --> 00:36:08.580
He leaches off other people.

409
00:36:08.720 --> 00:36:11.460
Stop saying that in front of his daughter.

410
00:36:11.840 --> 00:36:12.940
It's fine.

411
00:36:13.740 --> 00:36:16.340
That's what everyone thinks anyway.

412
00:36:22.520 --> 00:36:23.440
Do you want some?

413
00:36:24.880 --> 00:36:26.300
It's what Sleepy eats.

414
00:36:27.876 --> 00:36:29.075
This is Sleepy.

415
00:36:29.376 --> 00:36:30.475
Say hello.

416
00:36:31.753 --> 00:36:33.954
The baby's name is Sleepy?

417
00:36:34.460 --> 00:36:35.550
No. it's the fetus' name.

418
00:36:35.840 --> 00:36:38.120
It's like a nickname.

419
00:36:38.540 --> 00:36:42.380
Because his father is still too lazy
to come up with a name.

420
00:36:44.520 --> 00:36:45.460
Touch her belly.

421
00:36:46.060 --> 00:36:46.890
Right here.

422
00:36:48.540 --> 00:36:49.340
Go on.

423
00:36:55.260 --> 00:36:56.000
Felt that?

424
00:36:57.806 --> 00:36:59.222
I made that.

425
00:37:03.140 --> 00:37:04.120
You idiot.

426
00:37:04.121 --> 00:37:05.500
But it's true. isn't it?

427
00:37:18.560 --> 00:37:21.820
<i>Mr. Seok-woo. you called me
at a really bad time--</i>

428
00:37:21.820 --> 00:37:22.720
Wait. wait.

429
00:37:22.920 --> 00:37:24.780
I just need to ask you something.

430
00:37:25.040 --> 00:37:25.840
<i>What is it?</i>

431
00:37:27.280 --> 00:37:29.180
I'm aboard the KTX bound to Daejeon.

432
00:37:29.220 --> 00:37:30.585
<i>KTX?</i>

433
00:37:30.786 --> 00:37:33.150
<i>You're on the train right at this minute?</i>

434
00:37:33.300 --> 00:37:34.620
Yes and I'm almost there.

435
00:37:35.670 --> 00:37:38.853
Is it true that the army is deployed in Daejeon?

436
00:37:39.840 --> 00:37:41.290
<i>Yes. that's true.</i>

437
00:37:42.634 --> 00:37:45.943
Is that so? Then it must be safe there.

438
00:37:47.945 --> 00:37:50.206
<i>Well... That's...</i>

439
00:37:51.840 --> 00:37:54.920
Captain Min. it's safe there. right?

440
00:37:55.706 --> 00:38:00.802
<i>You will be quarantined once you arrive.</i>

441
00:38:00.920 --> 00:38:01.580
What?

442
00:38:05.520 --> 00:38:07.450
I'm with my daughter.

443
00:38:08.960 --> 00:38:12.120
Can you do something
to help me and my daughter?

444
00:38:14.100 --> 00:38:15.020
<i>But the thing is...</i>

445
00:38:15.020 --> 00:38:18.770
Just do me this favor and I'll pay you back.

446
00:38:20.760 --> 00:38:24.820
<i>Don't go to the main square.
and go to the east side. okay?</i>

447
00:38:24.900 --> 00:38:26.540
<i>I'll tell my men to meet you there.</i>

448
00:38:27.630 --> 00:38:29.800
All right. got it.
Thank you very much.

449
00:38:37.655 --> 00:38:39.255
Everyone's dead.

450
00:38:56.000 --> 00:38:56.880
What's going on?

451
00:38:57.740 --> 00:38:58.600
It's so quiet.

452
00:38:58.786 --> 00:38:59.786
Is this Daejeon?

453
00:39:07.304 --> 00:39:08.304
<i>There's nobody here.</i>

454
00:39:09.220 --> 00:39:10.440
Why isn't anybody here?

455
00:39:28.380 --> 00:39:29.240
Out of my way.

456
00:40:20.110 --> 00:40:21.911
What's going on back there?

457
00:40:24.920 --> 00:40:28.380
This is the violent situation
I've been telling you about.

458
00:40:28.620 --> 00:40:29.440
Conductor!

459
00:40:29.680 --> 00:40:31.480
- Are you the conductor?
- Yes.

460
00:40:32.300 --> 00:40:33.800
How many people can fit
inside the engine car?

461
00:40:34.100 --> 00:40:36.260
We must uncouple the trains
and head to Busan.

462
00:40:36.300 --> 00:40:37.400
- Uncouple?
- Yes!

463
00:40:37.580 --> 00:40:39.160
- We can't!
- Why not?

464
00:40:39.160 --> 00:40:40.760
It can't be done here.

465
00:40:42.270 --> 00:40:44.120
Then where's the army?

466
00:40:44.791 --> 00:40:45.791
The army...

467
00:40:46.020 --> 00:40:48.240
I only received a report about it.

468
00:40:48.260 --> 00:40:49.860
Where's my business card?

469
00:40:50.361 --> 00:40:51.361
Look.

470
00:40:51.580 --> 00:40:53.710
I'm the COO of Stallion Express.

471
00:40:53.920 --> 00:40:56.060
All routes to Daejeon had been cut off.

472
00:40:56.120 --> 00:40:57.880
All the buses are being rerouted.

473
00:40:58.040 --> 00:40:58.980
But for what?

474
00:40:59.060 --> 00:41:01.440
The city is under quarantine.

475
00:41:01.720 --> 00:41:03.520
They probably won't let us in.

476
00:41:03.800 --> 00:41:05.810
But Busan is still open.

477
00:41:05.911 --> 00:41:08.220
We must head straight to Busan. hurry!

478
00:41:08.240 --> 00:41:10.720
Wait. if what you're saying is true.

479
00:41:10.920 --> 00:41:12.515
we must take the others.

480
00:41:12.616 --> 00:41:15.210
- Take who?
- Let's check the station first.

481
00:41:16.020 --> 00:41:16.720
Hey!

482
00:41:20.021 --> 00:41:20.821
Dammit!

483
00:41:43.440 --> 00:41:46.240
RESTRICTED AREA

484
00:42:03.980 --> 00:42:05.120
Ignore them and let's go.

485
00:42:11.640 --> 00:42:12.640
Let's go. Soo-an.

486
00:42:12.680 --> 00:42:13.720
Where are we going?

487
00:42:15.020 --> 00:42:16.520
We're going this way.

488
00:42:16.640 --> 00:42:18.045
Just us?

489
00:42:18.046 --> 00:42:19.450
Yes. let's go.

490
00:42:25.740 --> 00:42:26.580
What is it?

491
00:42:28.350 --> 00:42:30.340
I'm going this way too.

492
00:42:31.117 --> 00:42:34.001
The main square is that way.
Just follow the others.

493
00:42:34.100 --> 00:42:35.760
I'm going with you.

494
00:42:36.815 --> 00:42:38.416
I heard you talking earlier.

495
00:42:39.040 --> 00:42:40.910
About the two of you being pulled out.

496
00:42:43.000 --> 00:42:45.130
I know the others
will be under quarantine.

497
00:42:47.140 --> 00:42:48.800
That's not true. Soo-an.

498
00:42:48.920 --> 00:42:50.340
I'm going to tell everyone!

499
00:42:50.500 --> 00:42:52.685
Soo-an. you don't have to.

500
00:42:52.886 --> 00:42:54.170
Of course. I do!

501
00:42:54.367 --> 00:42:56.635
Forget about them!
We're on our own now.

502
00:42:58.320 --> 00:43:02.010
Daddy. you only think about yourself.

503
00:43:04.400 --> 00:43:07.950
That's the reason why mom left.

504
00:43:27.260 --> 00:43:28.360
Soo-an...

505
00:43:30.360 --> 00:43:31.160
Hey!

506
00:43:31.380 --> 00:43:33.240
Here! Over here!

507
00:43:33.420 --> 00:43:34.550
We're here!

508
00:43:36.660 --> 00:43:38.740
Soo-an. stay right here.

509
00:43:59.800 --> 00:44:00.740
Goddamit!

510
00:44:02.720 --> 00:44:03.620
Hold on!

511
00:44:15.400 --> 00:44:17.230
Go back! Go back! Go!

512
00:44:35.260 --> 00:44:35.930
Captain Min?

513
00:44:35.940 --> 00:44:36.790
<i>Mr. Seok-woo!</i>

514
00:44:36.791 --> 00:44:37.640
I'm now in Daejeon.

515
00:44:37.640 --> 00:44:40.200
<i>Is everything all right there?
I can't contact my men!</i>

516
00:44:40.220 --> 00:44:41.260
What?

517
00:44:41.660 --> 00:44:42.580
<i>Hello?</i>

518
00:44:42.720 --> 00:44:44.020
Help me...

519
00:45:02.021 --> 00:45:03.721
<i>Soo-an!</i>

520
00:45:19.022 --> 00:45:20.022
Hurry! Hurry!

521
00:45:26.020 --> 00:45:27.185
Get inside! Hurry!

522
00:45:27.386 --> 00:45:28.650
Come on! Hurry!

523
00:45:40.570 --> 00:45:41.940
Come on! Hurry!

524
00:45:43.060 --> 00:45:43.820
Take this!

525
00:46:02.280 --> 00:46:03.540
Run! Come on!

526
00:46:08.920 --> 00:46:10.200
Hey. asshole! Come on!

527
00:46:18.846 --> 00:46:19.846
Faster!

528
00:46:22.100 --> 00:46:23.010
Hold them off!

529
00:46:56.840 --> 00:46:58.760
Over here! Run!

530
00:46:58.861 --> 00:47:01.080
This way! Hurry!

531
00:47:01.600 --> 00:47:02.620
Here! Here!

532
00:47:06.220 --> 00:47:07.340
This way!

533
00:47:08.512 --> 00:47:09.512
Come on!

534
00:47:09.720 --> 00:47:10.840
Hurry!

535
00:47:10.880 --> 00:47:13.200
Why aren't we leaving yet?

536
00:47:13.680 --> 00:47:15.560
There are still more people!

537
00:47:15.949 --> 00:47:16.949
Hurry up!

538
00:47:17.940 --> 00:47:19.420
Come this way!

539
00:47:20.720 --> 00:47:21.720
Hurry!

540
00:47:21.760 --> 00:47:23.140
Faster! Here!

541
00:47:36.580 --> 00:47:37.610
Grandma!

542
00:47:38.451 --> 00:47:39.451
Please get up!

543
00:47:42.652 --> 00:47:43.652
Sister!

544
00:47:49.940 --> 00:47:51.190
No. stop!

545
00:47:51.820 --> 00:47:52.800
But my sister!

546
00:48:01.490 --> 00:48:02.400
Hop on!

547
00:48:22.360 --> 00:48:23.220
Me too!

548
00:48:23.960 --> 00:48:25.710
Let me in!

549
00:48:26.520 --> 00:48:27.480
Please!

550
00:48:45.640 --> 00:48:47.020
How long do we have to wait?

551
00:48:47.121 --> 00:48:48.200
We must leave now!

552
00:48:48.220 --> 00:48:50.210
We can't! My friends aren't here yet!

553
00:48:51.460 --> 00:48:53.380
Those onboard must survive!

554
00:48:54.020 --> 00:48:54.740
Am I right?

555
00:49:01.860 --> 00:49:02.700
Conductor.

556
00:49:03.900 --> 00:49:04.970
Please...

557
00:49:05.271 --> 00:49:06.440
Please depart.

558
00:49:27.020 --> 00:49:28.480
Run! Let's go!

559
00:49:44.420 --> 00:49:45.660
Look. the train!

560
00:49:45.940 --> 00:49:46.800
Run faster!

561
00:50:06.295 --> 00:50:07.762
Snap out of it. you idiot!

562
00:50:37.220 --> 00:50:38.100
Watch out!

563
00:50:59.570 --> 00:51:04.260
Control. 101 could not dock
at Daejeon due to the outbreak.

564
00:51:04.520 --> 00:51:07.440
Advise which station is available to dock. over.

565
00:51:07.867 --> 00:51:12.697
<i>101. due to unstable communication.
it is difficult to advise.</i>

566
00:51:13.120 --> 00:51:18.080
Control. is 101 clear to reach Busan? Over.

567
00:51:20.902 --> 00:51:24.175
<i>101. we'll clear your route to Busan.</i>

568
00:51:24.240 --> 00:51:25.150
<i>Control center. out.</i>

569
00:51:26.680 --> 00:51:29.260
Please advise when you make contact with Busan.

570
00:51:30.360 --> 00:51:31.280
101. out.

571
00:52:47.220 --> 00:52:49.600
<i>Attention everyone.</i>

572
00:52:50.061 --> 00:52:55.137
<i>For the safety of everyone onboard.
this train will be headed to Busan.</i>

573
00:52:55.480 --> 00:52:57.180
<i>We won't make any stops.</i>

574
00:52:58.840 --> 00:53:00.960
Conductor. can you hear me?

575
00:53:01.520 --> 00:53:02.660
<i>Go ahead.</i>

576
00:53:03.240 --> 00:53:04.840
Were you able to contact Busan?

577
00:53:05.180 --> 00:53:08.010
<i>No. the communication is erratic.</i>

578
00:53:09.580 --> 00:53:11.500
Full speed. no matter what!

579
00:53:11.900 --> 00:53:13.860
We won't get in. otherwise. Understood?

580
00:53:21.820 --> 00:53:23.480
Young-Gook. where are you?

581
00:53:26.140 --> 00:53:29.060
I thought you were dead!

582
00:53:29.520 --> 00:53:30.560
I'm sorry!

583
00:53:33.010 --> 00:53:34.760
No one else made it!

584
00:53:36.120 --> 00:53:37.180
I'm sorry.

585
00:53:48.690 --> 00:53:50.720
- Honey?
<i>- Mister!</i>

586
00:53:51.844 --> 00:53:54.477
Why are you answering?
Where are you?

587
00:53:54.570 --> 00:53:56.820
<i>We're inside the washroom!</i>

588
00:53:56.860 --> 00:53:59.630
Washroom? Which car?

589
00:53:59.870 --> 00:54:02.520
<i>Well... it's...</i>

590
00:54:02.560 --> 00:54:04.860
<i>Car 13! Get your ass over here!</i>

591
00:54:04.941 --> 00:54:06.040
Honey!

592
00:54:09.620 --> 00:54:10.780
Was that my daughter?

593
00:54:10.900 --> 00:54:11.840
Is she okay?

594
00:54:12.340 --> 00:54:13.940
They're inside car 13's washroom.

595
00:54:29.140 --> 00:54:30.120
Gonna ram your way through?

596
00:54:32.510 --> 00:54:34.740
Let's say you got through and rescue them.

597
00:54:34.880 --> 00:54:36.380
how will you come back?

598
00:54:41.080 --> 00:54:42.350
In car 15.

599
00:54:44.020 --> 00:54:45.600
people are gathered there.

600
00:54:51.680 --> 00:54:53.580
CAR 9

601
00:55:10.820 --> 00:55:12.640
It's only four cars away.

602
00:55:14.739 --> 00:55:15.739
I'll take the lead.

603
00:55:17.520 --> 00:55:18.480
You. take the rear.

604
00:55:20.120 --> 00:55:21.120
And you. stay in the middle.

605
00:55:24.620 --> 00:55:26.580
Attack anyone coming from the back.

606
00:55:38.840 --> 00:55:40.880
I heard you're a fund manager.

607
00:55:43.960 --> 00:55:45.560
That means you're an expert

608
00:55:46.680 --> 00:55:48.620
in leaving useles people behind.

609
00:55:55.740 --> 00:55:57.380
We'll wait until we exit the next tunnel.

610
00:56:12.400 --> 00:56:13.510
Let's go.

611
00:57:24.820 --> 00:57:26.320
In here! Come on! Hurry!

612
00:57:28.520 --> 00:57:29.400
Let's go!

613
00:57:46.140 --> 00:57:46.960
Move.

614
00:59:30.880 --> 00:59:31.980
Move. move.

615
00:59:35.920 --> 00:59:39.500
They stopped once we entered the tunnel. right?

616
00:59:40.560 --> 00:59:42.080
It's probably because it turned dark.

617
00:59:42.120 --> 00:59:44.060
Yeah. I think so too.

618
00:59:47.000 --> 00:59:48.820
There are even more here.

619
00:59:49.960 --> 00:59:51.250
What do we do now?

620
00:59:52.640 --> 00:59:54.000
There's no way around it.

621
00:59:54.880 --> 00:59:55.800
Let's go.

622
00:59:59.900 --> 01:00:02.000
Hey. can I borrow your phone?

623
01:02:06.760 --> 01:02:08.180
Get that out of my face.

624
01:02:10.480 --> 01:02:11.640
Yo. asshole.

625
01:02:12.940 --> 01:02:16.960
Felt good to see your daughter
thanks to me. right?

626
01:02:17.020 --> 01:02:19.040
Are you grateful or what?

627
01:02:19.680 --> 01:02:21.800
Why is your ringtone so tacky?

628
01:02:23.000 --> 01:02:24.700
What's wrong with it?

629
01:02:26.620 --> 01:02:28.780
How do I change it?

630
01:02:30.422 --> 01:02:34.398
Am I funny? You little rat.

631
01:02:35.220 --> 01:02:36.360
How tall are you?

632
01:02:36.560 --> 01:02:37.760
181 cm.

633
01:02:38.740 --> 01:02:41.700
10km away at 300km/h...

634
01:02:41.760 --> 01:02:42.580
What?

635
01:02:45.900 --> 01:02:49.040
Two minutes.
The next tunnel can give us two minutes.

636
01:02:49.160 --> 01:02:51.230
- Can we do it?
- We have to. We have too...

637
01:02:52.530 --> 01:02:57.660
If we miss this one.
there's another tunnel in 3 km.

638
01:02:58.580 --> 01:03:01.020
I bet you never get to play with your daughter.

639
01:03:02.980 --> 01:03:04.600
When she gets older.

640
01:03:06.140 --> 01:03:09.090
she'll understand
why you're working so hard.

641
01:03:11.220 --> 01:03:14.430
Fathers always get the bad rap
and without praise

642
01:03:15.230 --> 01:03:17.540
but it's all about sacrifice. right?

643
01:03:21.070 --> 01:03:24.200
What's with that look?
Did I sound really cool?

644
01:03:32.820 --> 01:03:34.440
People rescued.
Heading over now.

645
01:03:35.951 --> 01:03:37.550
My friend's coming here!

646
01:03:39.200 --> 01:03:40.180
What did you say?

647
01:03:40.210 --> 01:03:43.060
My friend from another car
is coming here.

648
01:03:43.590 --> 01:03:45.580
- Who's coming?
- My friend!

649
01:03:45.880 --> 01:03:49.380
He was in car 9
and he was able to rescue other people.

650
01:03:49.820 --> 01:03:50.660
Rescued?

651
01:03:52.560 --> 01:03:54.825
From there to here?

652
01:03:55.626 --> 01:03:57.490
You're saying he survived all that?

653
01:03:58.280 --> 01:03:59.480
Without any injuries?

654
01:04:01.160 --> 01:04:02.700
Are you sure they're not infected?

655
01:04:04.070 --> 01:04:06.680
Are you damn sure they're not infected?

656
01:04:08.300 --> 01:04:10.000
What do you mean?

657
01:04:10.140 --> 01:04:12.770
Look. look at them.

658
01:04:13.480 --> 01:04:14.880
At a moment like this.

659
01:04:15.280 --> 01:04:19.830
nobody knows
what happened to their families.

660
01:04:20.560 --> 01:04:25.370
We don't even know
if your damn friends are infected!

661
01:04:25.780 --> 01:04:28.490
And you want us to allow them here? Huh?

662
01:04:32.940 --> 01:04:34.680
I don't believe this.

663
01:04:44.400 --> 01:04:45.380
Sir.

664
01:04:47.940 --> 01:04:50.100
please say something.

665
01:04:51.160 --> 01:04:52.720
They'll be here soon.

666
01:04:54.880 --> 01:04:56.360
Sir!

667
01:04:57.361 --> 01:04:58.561
Sir...

668
01:08:44.600 --> 01:08:45.720
Get over here.

669
01:08:54.940 --> 01:08:55.720
One!

670
01:08:58.340 --> 01:08:59.160
Two!

671
01:09:05.960 --> 01:09:06.760
Run!

672
01:09:20.380 --> 01:09:21.460
Jin-hee! Jin-hee!

673
01:09:24.930 --> 01:09:26.300
Hurry the hell up!

674
01:09:36.400 --> 01:09:37.300
Open up!

675
01:09:38.240 --> 01:09:40.860
Hey! Open this door!

676
01:09:42.620 --> 01:09:43.240
Jin-hee!

677
01:09:43.600 --> 01:09:44.380
Open this door!

678
01:10:00.780 --> 01:10:03.950
- Open up!
- Jin-hee! Jin-hee!

679
01:10:14.540 --> 01:10:15.970
Open it now!

680
01:10:17.040 --> 01:10:18.100
It won't budge!

681
01:10:18.370 --> 01:10:19.520
I can't open it!

682
01:10:19.649 --> 01:10:20.649
Smash it!

683
01:10:21.620 --> 01:10:22.480
Stand back!

684
01:10:29.350 --> 01:10:30.480
Hurry up!

685
01:10:35.160 --> 01:10:36.360
Dammit!

686
01:11:00.860 --> 01:11:02.220
You stupid idiots!

687
01:11:16.060 --> 01:11:16.890
Come on!

688
01:11:28.600 --> 01:11:29.540
In-Gil!

689
01:11:35.200 --> 01:11:36.100
Young-Gook!

690
01:11:39.700 --> 01:11:40.900
Stand back!

691
01:11:40.920 --> 01:11:41.800
Young-Gook!

692
01:12:16.660 --> 01:12:17.740
Stay away!

693
01:12:24.920 --> 01:12:28.680
Stay back. honey.
Please. go.

694
01:12:35.260 --> 01:12:36.640
Buddy. hey!

695
01:12:38.980 --> 01:12:40.160
Take her and go.

696
01:12:41.360 --> 01:12:42.820
Hurry and go.

697
01:12:44.380 --> 01:12:45.920
I said go. asshole!

698
01:12:47.800 --> 01:12:49.840
I'm getting tired.
Just hurry and go.

699
01:12:53.580 --> 01:12:56.840
Please. take care of her. Okay?

700
01:12:58.200 --> 01:13:01.880
I'll hold them off. just go!

701
01:13:12.300 --> 01:13:14.120
I'm... I'm sorry.

702
01:13:24.993 --> 01:13:26.993
We have to go. now!

703
01:13:29.010 --> 01:13:30.080
Yoon Soo-yun!

704
01:13:32.600 --> 01:13:34.420
That's our baby's name.

705
01:13:35.680 --> 01:13:36.720
Got it?

706
01:15:36.939 --> 01:15:38.207
Why did you do it?

707
01:15:40.810 --> 01:15:41.980
You bastard!

708
01:15:43.948 --> 01:15:45.416
We could have saved them!

709
01:15:48.110 --> 01:15:48.960
Why?

710
01:15:50.420 --> 01:15:51.980
He's infected!

711
01:15:53.540 --> 01:15:55.280
He's one of them!

712
01:15:55.860 --> 01:15:57.090
This guy's infected!

713
01:15:57.600 --> 01:15:59.520
His eyes! Look at his eyes!

714
01:15:59.700 --> 01:16:01.940
He'll become one of them!

715
01:16:02.360 --> 01:16:03.790
Do you all want to die?!

716
01:16:04.100 --> 01:16:05.520
We need to throw them out!

717
01:16:16.480 --> 01:16:19.270
Those of you who just arrived.

718
01:16:20.292 --> 01:16:22.625
I don't think you can stay with us.

719
01:16:24.540 --> 01:16:26.480
Please move to the vestibule.

720
01:16:41.680 --> 01:16:42.580
Hurry!

721
01:16:47.780 --> 01:16:48.700
Get out!

722
01:16:55.380 --> 01:16:56.720
Get out now!

723
01:16:58.720 --> 01:16:59.540
Hurry up!

724
01:17:00.720 --> 01:17:01.640
Move!

725
01:17:04.220 --> 01:17:05.480
Go!

726
01:17:06.200 --> 01:17:07.420
Leave us!

727
01:17:07.800 --> 01:17:09.000
Get the hell out!

728
01:17:11.698 --> 01:17:12.698
Leave now!

729
01:17:14.640 --> 01:17:15.680
Hurry!

730
01:17:19.360 --> 01:17:22.200
Jin-hee. it'll be safer for you to stay here.

731
01:17:22.200 --> 01:17:25.210
No. I don't want to stay.

732
01:17:26.810 --> 01:17:27.961
I'm going with you.

733
01:17:27.980 --> 01:17:28.700
But...

734
01:17:29.220 --> 01:17:30.530
Get the hell out!

735
01:17:31.120 --> 01:17:32.920
What are you waiting for?

736
01:17:33.540 --> 01:17:34.900
Okay. let's go.

737
01:17:37.620 --> 01:17:40.000
Get out! All of you! Hurry!

738
01:17:40.676 --> 01:17:41.676
Get out!

739
01:17:42.140 --> 01:17:44.020
Get out of here!

740
01:18:02.060 --> 01:18:02.940
Let's go.

741
01:18:40.480 --> 01:18:41.910
Tie it faster!

742
01:18:43.000 --> 01:18:44.100
More ties! Neckties!

743
01:18:45.420 --> 01:18:47.020
Shut up! I'm working on it!

744
01:19:02.540 --> 01:19:03.680
You've always been like that.

745
01:19:04.640 --> 01:19:05.870
Always.

746
01:19:07.240 --> 01:19:11.320
Always helping others
instead of yourself.

747
01:19:15.600 --> 01:19:17.520
Why did you live your life that way?

748
01:19:19.200 --> 01:19:21.480
What's the point?

749
01:19:22.850 --> 01:19:24.180
So stupid...

750
01:19:31.420 --> 01:19:32.910
Shut up! Be quiet!

751
01:19:34.140 --> 01:19:35.460
Stay on your seat!

752
01:19:36.480 --> 01:19:38.940
What a load of shit.

753
01:19:43.770 --> 01:19:46.000
Finish up and do the other side too.

754
01:19:56.980 --> 01:20:00.880
Thank you for everything.

755
01:20:02.600 --> 01:20:03.520
That woman...

756
01:20:03.560 --> 01:20:04.960
Stop that woman!

757
01:20:59.060 --> 01:21:01.700
Control. this is Busan-bound 101!

758
01:21:01.800 --> 01:21:03.740
Requesting update on Busan. Over.

759
01:21:05.440 --> 01:21:06.370
Control?

760
01:21:07.120 --> 01:21:07.980
Control!

761
01:22:34.800 --> 01:22:36.460
Today's your birthday.

762
01:22:41.157 --> 01:22:42.157
Don't worry.

763
01:22:43.040 --> 01:22:45.220
I'll take you to your mom.
no matter what happens.

764
01:22:49.300 --> 01:22:51.000
Daddy. aren't you scared?

765
01:22:56.940 --> 01:22:57.860
Of course. I am.

766
01:23:00.200 --> 01:23:01.150
I'm scared too.

767
01:23:06.310 --> 01:23:08.160
I was so scared.

768
01:23:08.980 --> 01:23:11.840
I thought I will never ever see you again.

769
01:23:14.200 --> 01:23:19.020
I practiced that song just for you.

770
01:23:23.360 --> 01:23:25.340
That's why I couldn't finish the song.

771
01:23:27.880 --> 01:23:29.560
Because I didn't see you there.

772
01:23:37.120 --> 01:23:39.360
Will you listen to me
when I finish the song?

773
01:23:54.580 --> 01:23:56.520
EX-WIFE

774
01:24:07.540 --> 01:24:12.000
<i>The person you're calling is not available.</i>

775
01:24:22.280 --> 01:24:25.740
ANALYST KIM

776
01:24:28.520 --> 01:24:29.600
Yes. Mr. Kim.

777
01:24:31.440 --> 01:24:33.300
<i>Have you arrived in Busan?</i>

778
01:24:33.345 --> 01:24:34.711
Not yet.

779
01:24:34.712 --> 01:24:36.078
Where are you? How are things there?

780
01:24:37.820 --> 01:24:40.100
<i>Busan succeeded with its initial defense.</i>

781
01:24:40.640 --> 01:24:43.480
What? Are you sure?

782
01:24:43.800 --> 01:24:45.260
Where did you hear that news?

783
01:24:46.300 --> 01:24:47.160
<i>Sir...</i>

784
01:24:48.180 --> 01:24:50.500
<i>All of these started with YT Biotech.</i>

785
01:24:53.000 --> 01:24:57.020
<i>That was our project.
We funded the plant that started all of these!</i>

786
01:25:01.420 --> 01:25:02.460
<i>Sir...</i>

787
01:25:03.340 --> 01:25:06.080
<i>Please tell me this isn't our fault.</i>

788
01:25:07.500 --> 01:25:10.800
<i>We were only doing our jobs. right?</i>

789
01:25:11.840 --> 01:25:13.980
<i>Is this my fault?</i>

790
01:25:17.500 --> 01:25:18.800
It's...

791
01:25:19.760 --> 01:25:21.120
It's not your fault.

792
01:25:25.192 --> 01:25:26.192
<i>Thank you.</i>

793
01:25:28.420 --> 01:25:29.280
Mr. Kim--

794
01:27:14.580 --> 01:27:16.320
Attention please.

795
01:27:16.740 --> 01:27:20.470
<i>Due to a blockage on our track.</i>

796
01:27:20.960 --> 01:27:23.200
<i>we have stopped at East Daegu Station.</i>

797
01:27:23.460 --> 01:27:27.180
<i>We should either wait for the rescue team.</i>

798
01:27:27.240 --> 01:27:32.060
<i>or we will have to go to Busan using another train.</i>

799
01:27:32.680 --> 01:27:34.700
<i>As soon as I end this announcement.</i>

800
01:27:35.000 --> 01:27:40.580
<i>I will find a working train
and park it on the leftmost track.</i>

801
01:27:40.640 --> 01:27:41.380
What's happening?

802
01:27:41.400 --> 01:27:44.100
<i>I repeat. leftmost track.</i>

803
01:27:44.470 --> 01:27:46.528
If you're alive...

804
01:27:47.129 --> 01:27:49.087
Please transfer safely.

805
01:27:51.140 --> 01:27:52.200
Godspeed.

806
01:28:58.220 --> 01:28:59.880
Will there be rescue coming?

807
01:29:02.740 --> 01:29:04.700
I heard that Busan is safe.

808
01:29:07.300 --> 01:29:08.620
We need to go now.

809
01:30:54.140 --> 01:30:55.060
Is the coast clear?

810
01:30:58.200 --> 01:30:59.050
Yes.

811
01:31:02.269 --> 01:31:03.269
You go ahead.

812
01:31:27.860 --> 01:31:29.540
We need to find a way across.

813
01:31:53.490 --> 01:31:54.600
What the...?

814
01:32:07.280 --> 01:32:08.200
Over here!

815
01:32:45.560 --> 01:32:46.440
No...

816
01:32:46.700 --> 01:32:47.560
Oh no...

817
01:32:49.980 --> 01:32:51.380
What do we do now?

818
01:32:52.220 --> 01:32:54.310
We have to go. Come on.

819
01:33:02.560 --> 01:33:04.060
Jin-hee. hurry!

